Russia

Russia is yet another country where you must be careful with whom, and where, you speak. You can be taken into police custody and held for as long as 24 hours, or even 2-3 days (if you are lucky, you will only be fined). An illegally held prisoner spends much of their time in solitary confinement. Sued for libel for a simple article you published? The cost? Don’t worry – it’s only a few thousand dollars in court costs and fines.

A sad state of affairs and repressive politics is justified by “Russian special service agents” and “notorious Russian hooligans who reign throughout Europe.”

Because of this, accommodations cost about as much as a month of rent in New York City. Luxury is out of the question, and any tourist facing bribery charges will find their travel plans curtailed to say the least.

Turkey
